# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Lesson 14 -- Azure Speech + Azure OpenAI via Microsoft Foundry (keyless auth)
#
# KEYLESS: there are NO key lines in this file. Auth flows through
# DefaultAzureCredential, which picks up your `az login` session on a
# developer laptop and a managed identity in Azure. The signed-in user (or
# managed identity) must hold the "Cognitive Services User" role on the
# AIServices resource -- Deploy-Lesson14-Infrastructure.ps1 auto-assigns it.
#
# NOTE on the keyless auth asymmetry (the most-tested Lesson 14 nuance):
#
#   STT (SpeechRecognizer):
#     Uses SpeechConfig(token_credential=..., endpoint=SPEECH_ENDPOINT)
#     The SDK exchanges the credential for a token automatically.
#
#   TTS (SpeechSynthesizer):
#     The synthesizer does NOT accept a TokenCredential directly.
#     It needs the auth_token built as: "aad#{SPEECH_RESOURCE_ID}#{entraToken}"
#     plus the region string. The script builds this token at runtime.
#
#   Chat (AzureOpenAI):
#     Uses AzureOpenAI(azure_ad_token_provider=get_bearer_token_provider(...))
#
# How to get these values (after Deploy-Lesson14-Infrastructure.ps1):
#
#   SPEECH_ENDPOINT -- custom-domain Speech endpoint:
#     az cognitiveservices account show \
#       -g rg-ai901-lesson14-demo -n <your-resource-name> \
#       --query properties.endpoint -o tsv
#     Must be https://<name>.cognitiveservices.azure.com/ (custom subdomain).
#     A regional endpoint will reject Entra token auth on the STT recognizer.
#
#   SPEECH_REGION -- short region code, e.g. swedencentral, eastus2:
#     az cognitiveservices account show \
#       -g rg-ai901-lesson14-demo -n <your-resource-name> \
#       --query location -o tsv
#
#   SPEECH_RESOURCE_ID -- full ARM resource ID for the TTS aad# token:
#     az cognitiveservices account show \
#       -g rg-ai901-lesson14-demo -n <your-resource-name> \
#       --query id -o tsv
#
#   AOAI_ENDPOINT -- Azure OpenAI endpoint (openai.azure.com form):
#     the deploy script prints this; or replace cognitiveservices.azure.com
#     with openai.azure.com in the Speech endpoint URL.
#
#   AOAI_DEPLOYMENT -- chat deployment name (e.g. gpt-4o)
#   AOAI_API_VERSION -- pinned data-plane API version
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
SPEECH_ENDPOINT=https://YOUR-RESOURCE-NAME.cognitiveservices.azure.com/
SPEECH_REGION=YOUR-REGION
SPEECH_RESOURCE_ID=/subscriptions/<your-subscription-id>/resourceGroups/<your-rg>/providers/Microsoft.CognitiveServices/accounts/<your-speech-resource>
AOAI_ENDPOINT=https://YOUR-RESOURCE-NAME.openai.azure.com/
AOAI_DEPLOYMENT=gpt-4o
AOAI_API_VERSION=2024-10-21

# NEVER commit the real .env file to source control.
